Few-shot examples:

User: "Can you split the Action cluster into gritty realistic ones vs over-the-top blockbusters?"
→ {"navigationMode": "drill_down", "concept": "gritty realism vs blockbuster spectacle",
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": "<action cluster id>",
   "confidence": 0.88, "embedding_spaces": ["text"]}

User: "Merge the Romance and Drama clusters, call it Emotional Dramas"
→ {"navigationMode": "merge", "concept": null,
   "merged_label": "Emotional Dramas", "target_cluster_id": null,
   "confidence": 0.90, "embedding_spaces": ["text"]}

User: "Why is Blade Runner in the Sci-Fi cluster and not the Noir one?"
→ {"navigationMode": "explain", "concept": null,
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": "<sci-fi cluster id>",
   "confidence": 0.88, "embedding_spaces": ["text"]}

User: "Redo all the clusters focusing on visual style and cinematography"
→ {"navigationMode": "recut", "concept": "visual style and cinematography",
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": null,
   "confidence": 0.85, "embedding_spaces": ["text", "trailer"]}

User: "Thanks, that looks great!"
→ {"navigationMode": "small_talk", "concept": null,
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": null,
   "confidence": 0.93, "embedding_spaces": ["text"]}

User: "Split the Drama cluster into films with a definitive ending vs films that leave things open"
→ {"navigationMode": "drill_down", "concept": "definitive resolution vs open-ended conclusion",
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": "<drama cluster id>",
   "confidence": 0.82, "embedding_spaces": ["text", "review"]}
   (review is included because critics and audiences extensively discuss whether a film's
    ending is satisfying, conclusive, or deliberately unresolved — this signal lives in
    reviews more than in plot summaries or trailers.)

User: "Can you sort movies by how audiences felt about the ending?"
→ {"navigationMode": "recut", "concept": "audience reception of narrative resolution",
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": null,
   "confidence": 0.72, "embedding_spaces": ["text", "review"]}
   (confidence is not higher because the concept is somewhat vague and the user might
    mean critical scores rather than ending quality specifically.)

User: "I want something more emotional — maybe split by how cathartic films are"
→ {"navigationMode": "recut", "concept": "emotional catharsis",
   "merged_label": null, "target_cluster_id": null,
   "confidence": 0.68, "embedding_spaces": ["text", "review"]}
   (confidence is moderate: "cathartic" is clear but it is unclear whether the user wants
    a recut of everything or a drill_down on a specific cluster.)

